Note on third-party content:

- Vendor binary files (Axon Servo Programming Software exe, .sfw firmware
  files) and any decompiled outputs derived from them are NOT licensed
  under MIT and are not redistributed in this repository's source tree.
  They are downloaded directly from the vendor by the user and remain
  subject to the vendor's terms.
- Decompiled functions in research/static-analysis/ghidra_out/ are
  research artifacts derived from the vendor binary; they are kept in
  the repository for reproducibility of the reverse-engineering work
  but are not part of the MIT-licensed source distribution.
- Third-party tools used during research (Ghidra, Saleae Logic 2, libusb,
  hidapi, Bun, Parallels) retain their own licenses; see docs/licenses.md
  (added in issue #8).
